						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#139;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#135;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#166;&amp;#232;&amp;#168;&amp;#152;Zero (The War Chronicles of Ganymede Zero) is a two player card game from Japan in which Mechs are enhanced with transparent cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The battle for new resources discovered on Jupiter's moon Ganymede was fierce: in 208X the battle using humanoid weapons called Mechs began in earnest, and Mechs with various equipment appeared on the scene.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a card game in which players use transparent cards to equip three Mechs and fight battles with the equipped Mechs; each Mech can be equipped with three different types of equipment: right hand, left hand and back.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who will be the first to defeat the opposing unit?&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The publisher says:&amp;#10;In the year 208X, over the resources discovered on Jupiter, a war broke out between the Nyekundu force and the Vert force.&amp;#10;On the satellite Ganymede, the foothold for mining the resources on Jupiter, humanoid battle weapons called Mechs were engaged in battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game, players, each as the captain of a platoon, aim to destroy the enemy force.&amp;#10;The player who destroys all three Mechs of their opponent wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
